books.title: The Great Gatsby
books.author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
books.description: Set in the Jazz Age, this classic novel tells the story of Jay Gatsby's quest to win back his lost love, Daisy Buchanan, and his tragic downfall.

books.title: To Kill a Mockingbird
books.author: Harper Lee
books.description: Set in the 1930s, this Pulitzer Prize-winning novel tells the story of a young girl named Scout and her father, a lawyer named Atticus Finch, who defends an African American man falsely accused of a crime.

books.title: The Catcher in the Rye
books.author: J.D. Salinger
books.description: This novel follows Holden Caulfield, a teenage boy expelled from his prep school, as he wanders around New York City, grappling with alienation, identity, and loss.
